President Obama has declared a state of emergency in West Virginia and ordered federal aid to help with the chemical spill emergency that began on January 9, 2014. The Department of Homeland Security and FEMA will coordinate disaster relief efforts to assist the local population and provide emergency measures to save lives and protect property and public health and safety. FEMA will identify and provide necessary equipment and resources, and emergency protective measures will be funded at 75 percent by the federal government. Michael J. Lapinski has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area.